.\" Manpage for Simple Shell.
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "16 April 2020" "1.0" "Simple Shell man page"
.SH NAME
hsh - command interpreter (Shell)

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh  [command_string | options or flags | file or argument]

.SH DESCRIPTION

.B The hsh utility is a command language interpreter that shall execute commands read from a command line string, the standard input, or a specified file.
.B It is known as Command Line Interpreter, program that accepts commands from the keyboard and then executes either by itself or by passing it on to the operating system.

.SH SYNTAX

.B hsh [command] [âˆ’o option]...[+o option]...[command_file [argument...]]

.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
.B shell should work like this in interactive mode:

.RS 3
$ ./hsh
.br
#cisfun$ echo "Hello World"
.br
Hello World
.br
#cisfun$
.RE

.B But also in non-interactive mode:

.RS 3
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.br
File1   File2   File3
.RE

.SH RESERVED WORDS
.B exit:
End the program, exit the shell.

.B env:
Displays the enviroment variables.

.SH SEE ALSO
.I sh (1)
.I bash (1)
.I ksh(1)
.I csh(1)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

